Sarah Gray Rafferty (born December 6, 1972) is an American television and film actress. She is known mainly for her role as Donna on the USA Network legal drama "Suits". She has appeared in many other television series. Other roles include the 2007 TV movie "What If God Were the Sun?" and the 2011 movie "Small, Beautifully Moving Parts".
Personal.
Rafferty grew up as the youngest of four children (all girls) in the Riverside neighborhood of Greenwich, Connecticut. She credits her mother, the Chairwoman of the English Department at Convent of the Sacred Heart school, and her father, who enjoys two successful careers in finance and oil painting, for cultivating her passion for the arts.
Rafferty majored in English and Theatre at Hamilton College, studied theatre abroad in London and at the University of Oxford during her junior year, and, after graduating magna cum laude from Hamilton, went on to study at the Yale School of Drama, receiving a Master of Fine Arts. She met her husband, stock analyst Aleksanteri Olli-Pekka 'Santtu' Seppälä, at Yale University, and they were married on June 23, 2001, at the Roman Catholic church of St. Mary in Greenwich, Connecticut. The couple have two daughters, Oona (b. 2007) and Iris (b. 2011).
She and her "Suits" co-star Gabriel Macht have been good friends for nearly 20 years. During the filming of the series in Toronto, they lived together for the first season.
